            <td>
            <h6>In this artist's conception of plasmon energy expansion thermometry (PEET), the focused electron beam is shown penetrating a 100-nm wide, heated aluminum wire atop a thin glass window. The electron beam has sufficient spatial resolution to detect atomic-scale grain boundaries in the poly-crystalline aluminum. (Credit: USC CEMMA &amp; UCLA Regan Group)</h6>
            </td>
